                     <interp inst="def2-1531-18410510" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">SAMUEL MARKS</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18410510-1531-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18410510-1531-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18410510-1531-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp> stealing, on the <rs id="t18410510-cd-243" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410510-1531-offence-1 t18410510-cd-243"></join>8th of May</rs>, 1 purse, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 4 sovereigns, and 3 shillings; the property of <persName id="t18410510-name-1336" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1336" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1336" type="surname" value="PETHERAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1336" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410510-1531-offence-1 t18410510-name-1336"></join>William Petheram</persName>, from the person of <persName id="t18410510-name-1337" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1337" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1337" type="surname" value="PETHERAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1337" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410510-1531-offence-1 t18410510-name-1337"></join>Charlotte Petheram</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410510-name-1338" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1338" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1338" type="surname" value="PETHERAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1338" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>CHARLOTTE PETHERAM</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of William Petheram, and live in West-square, Lambeth. On Saturday night, the 8th of May, I went to a fishmonger's stall near the Marsh-gate, to make a purchase—I saw the two prisoners standing by me—I had my purse out to pay for what I had bought—it contained four sovereigns and three shillings—Marks looked very bard at me—he put his hand across me, and took up the crab that I had bought, and felt the weight of it—he then put it down, and offered 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for three small ones—I tied up ray purse, and put it into my pocket—I turned from the stand, and in a moment I felt Hyams's hand in my pocket—I turned round and told him he was robbing me—the prisoners were standing together—I did not see them talk—Hyams said, "I am not"—I felt my pocket, and my purse was gone—he ran from me, and the mob secured him in a shop—Marks came over, and tried to defend him, and get him from me—he said he was not the person who had robbed me—I am sure his hand was in my pocket—the purse has not been found—there were several more with them—they are the only two I can swear to.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> This is a great thoroughfare, is it not? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—it was about eight o'clock in the evening—there is a kind of market there—I never went to any other stall—there were more near to that—I did not talk to the prisoners—I thought they both looked suspi<lb></lb>ciously at my purse, and I tied it up, and put it into my pocket—Marks' hand was not in my pocket—I never lost sight of biro—Marks vindicated Hyams, and said I ought to let him go—I did not consent to that.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Were there others standing by? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> There were, but I did not notice them—I felt Hyams's hand in my pocket, and turned and spoke to him—I had a shawl on, not a velvet mantle—my pocket was behind—I saw Hyams's hand inside my drees—I did not take him—I was in hopes he had not taken my purse till I found it was gone.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410510-name-1339" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1339" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1339" type="surname" value="MAXWELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1339" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MAXWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Joseph Harvey, in the Westminster-road. I saw Hyams near the prosecutrix—he ran away to Mr. Barber's</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184105100175"></xptr>
               <p>the grocer—Marks came up and said, "If he has got your purse, why don't you search him?"—the prosecutrix said Marks was with the prisoner—he said he was a respectable man and kept a shop in the neighbourhood.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Could he have thrown any thing away? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He could have done it—there was a mob.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did he not say he had friends who kept a shop in the neighbourhood? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.</p>
               <p>(Marks received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">MARKS—
<rs id="t18410510-1531-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
